latestPosts.caption:
When I moved to Canada, I thought I was ready. Mature enough to handle life, people, choices. I kept thinking, “How hard can it really be?”
But Canada HUMBLED me in every possible way. 😂

This journey has tested me, emotionally, mentally, deeply.
I didn’t choose to be this independent; I just had no other choice.
Fake friends, college stress, a relationship falling apart…I felt broken from inside.

And in the middle of all that chaos, I found someone..ME!
The only person who could save me was me.

I cried. I screamed. I asked the universe, “Why me?”
But the more I drowned in that pain, the more I stayed stuck.

One day, I stopped waiting to be rescued. I chose myself. ✨
As a people pleaser, choosing me felt selfish. I carried so much guilt.
But not anymore.

No, I’m not at my happiest here.
I’m still going back and forth with healing, some days are good, some days feel heavy. And that’s okay.
Because I know it’ll take time.
But now… I believe in myself. 🌸

I’m also so grateful for the friends and family I have here, the ones who showed up for me, supported me, and held space for me.♥️

This place has showed me how low I can fall and still rise. 💫

If you’re going through something right now and feel like it’s the end please know it’s not. 🫶🏻

Hold on.
You’ve got you.
And that’s more powerful than you think💌
